Greenland Energy Company selected Halliburton to provide integrated consulting, logistics, and comprehensive well and drilling services for the first onshore exploration wells in Greenland’s undrilled Jameson Land Basin.
Halliburton secured a multibillion dollar contract from YPF in Argentina’s Vaca Muerta shale, covering bundled unconventional completions services and including the first international use of ZEUS electric fracturing and the OCTIV Auto Frac digital operating environment.
Halliburton entered a collaboration with PETRONAS Suriname Exploration & Production BV and Valaris to support development of Suriname assets, combining basin expertise, offshore drilling capability, and Halliburton technology across the project lifecycle.
Between January 1 and March 31, 2026, Halliburton repurchased 2,903,638 shares for US$100m, and it plans to ask shareholders on May 20, 2026 to approve removing the Pass Through Voting Provision from the Halliburton Energy Services Inc. charter.
Fair value moved from US$39.30 to US$41.64.
Revenue growth assumption moved from roughly 2.03% to 3.52%.
Net profit margin assumption adjusted from about 11.07% to 10.61%.
Future P/E multiple moved from 14.47x to 15.13x.
Discount rate moved from 7.46% to 7.40%.
